3:03PM (64-06) Defendant James R Houck appeared by video.  Attorney Larry David Steen in court for James R Houck.  Plaintiff State of Wisconsin Samuel Berg in court. 
State called to the stand as a witness Deputy Sheriff Brandon Steffen.
Brandon Steffen duly sworn by the clerk and testified on direct examination by ADA Berg. Witness identified the defendant on the video in Court.
Exhibit #1 marked, identified and discussed in Court.
Exhibit #1 offered and received by the Court.
3:13PM - Cross examination by Attorney Steen.
3:21AM - Argument by ADA Berg.
No argument by the defense.
Court finds probable cause that a felony has been committed and that the defendant likely committed it and binds him over to stand trial on the charges. 
Arraignment held in open Court.
Defense acknowledge receipt of the Information, waived reading and plead not guilty to all charges.
Defense request Speedy Trial.

Adj. 3:27PM
Signed bond filed with the court.

Defendant James R Houck in court, in custody by video.  Attorney Larry David Steen in court for James R Houck.  Prosecuting attorney Vivien L. TenHaken in court for the State of Wisconsin. Previous cash bond to cover all files. Rights given and preliminary hearing requested within time period. Minutes filed.
Preliminary hearing scheduled for October 21, 2022 at 03:00 pm.
